This is a mirror of http://www.vim.org/scripts/script.php?script_id=3731

         When you execute a command, its result is showing in the command line.
         Sometimes you want to yank it, but unfortunately you can not edit the result in the command line.

         Putcmd can help you. 
         It inserts the command and its result after the current line. Then you can edit them easily.

Tutorial
         :Putcmd command

         :Putcmd colo
         :Putcmd set guifont?
         :Putcmd set tabstop?
